---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | The Daily Chronicle">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">The Story Behind the Byline</h1>
      <div class="w-16 h-1 bg-ink mx-auto mb-6"></div>
    </header>
    
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <div class="mb-8 float-right ml-8 mb-4 w-64">
        <img 
          src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/1516680/pexels-photo-1516680.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1" 
          alt="Author portrait" 
          class="w-full h-auto grayscale"
          width="400"
          height="500"
        />
        <p class="text-sm italic text-center mt-2">Capturing moments, one frame at a time</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="font-serif text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
        <p class="italic">
          In the halls of A. G. Patil Polytechnic,<br>
          Where dreams take flight and codes align,<br>
          A story unfolds, both technical and poetic,<br>
          Of a soul who dares to intertwine
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <p>I'm Akhil Karampuri, a graduate in Computer Science from A. G. Patil Polytechnic Institute, Solapur. Like a well-balanced algorithm, I find joy in the harmony of diverse interests: coding that brings ideas to life, photography that captures fleeting moments, and words that weave stories through my blog posts.</p>
      
      <p>They say I'm average at everything, but perhaps that's my superpower - the ability to find the extraordinary in the ordinary, to see the poetry in programming, and to crack jokes that somehow always land. My friends often tell me my humor is my signature, a thread of joy that runs through all my creations.</p>
      
      <h2>The Code Poet</h2>
      
      <p>In the world of coding, I'm like a curious explorer, always eager to learn and create. Each project is a new adventure, a chance to turn ideas into reality. My approach to programming is like writing poetry - finding elegance in simplicity, beauty in functionality.</p>
      
      <h2>Through the Lens</h2>
      
      <p>Photography is my silent poetry. Through my lens, I capture the stories that words sometimes can't tell. Each click is a moment frozen in time, a perspective shared, a memory preserved. My portfolio showcases these visual tales, each image speaking its own thousand words.</p>
      
      <h2>The Storyteller</h2>
      
      <p>My blog is where all these elements converge - technical insights, visual stories, and the occasional joke that makes my readers smile. It's a space where I share not just what I know, but how I see the world - through the eyes of someone who finds joy in being a jack of all trades.</p>
      
      <div class="font-serif text-xl leading-relaxed mt-8">
        <p class="italic">
          So here I stand, average yet unique,<br>
          A coder, photographer, and writer in sync,<br>
          Finding humor in life's every peak,<br>
          Making memories, one story at a time to think
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>